  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the chorizo slices and cook until browned, about 3 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, garlic, and red bell pepper, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the San-Marzano tomatoes and stir to combine.",
    "In a separate pan, warm the lettuce leaves over medium heat for about 3 minutes on each side, or until slightly wilted.",
    "To assemble the wrap, spread a layer of cream cheese on the bottom half of the lettuce leaf, then add the chorizo mixture, followed by a sprinkle of feta cheese, smoked paprika, and chopped cilantro if using.",
    "Drizzle with lime juice if using, and fold the top half of the lettuce leaf over the filling to enclose the wrap.",
    "Steam the wrap in a steamer basket for 2-3 minutes, or until the lettuce is tender and the filling is heated through.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!"
  ],
